{"parentUuid":"77d6070b-3d08-448b-b951-ea513e55c322","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/yahelraviv/compass","sessionId":"27b16fb5-b576-43fc-9679-48f034ac8885","version":"2.1.69","gitBranch":"main","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Step 1: Run the DB schema migration\n                                                                                                       \n  Context: This is a Next.js + Prisma monorepo deployed on Vercel, with a Supabase PostgreSQL database.\n   The Prisma schema lives at packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma. We recently changed the schema: the\n  ReflectionSession model had its monthKey field changed from required to optional (nullable), the\n  unique constraint @@unique([studentId, monthKey]) was removed, and a new templateId and sessionNumber\n   field were added. A new model ReflectionTemplate was also added. None of this has been applied to\n  the production database yet.\n\n  What to do: Run prisma db push against the production Supabase database to apply the schema changes.\n  This is safe — all changes are additive (adding nullable columns, a new table, removing a unique\n  constraint).\n\n  What you need: The DATABASE_URL and DIRECT_URL values from your Vercel environment variables (visible\n   in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables). These are Supabase connection strings.\n  DIRECT_URL is the direct (non-pooled) connection and is what you need for migrations.\n\n  Command to run from the root of the monorepo:\n  DIRECT_URL=\"<your-direct-url>\" DATABASE_URL=\"<your-database-url>\" pnpm --filter @compass/db db:push\n\n  If that doesn't work, try:\n  DIRECT_URL=\"<your-direct-url>\" DATABASE_URL=\"<your-database-url>\" pnpm --filter @compass/db exec\n  prisma db push\n\n  Expected outcome: Prisma connects to Supabase and applies the schema changes. It should print\n  something like \"Your database is now in sync with your Prisma schema.\" No data will be lost."},"uuid":"784837da-ad46-451c-bb7d-ae15efa6496b","timestamp":"2026-03-05T04:26:45.586Z","permissionMode":"default"}
